ADDITIONAL NOTICES:

This software accesses and aggregates liturgical data from various Catholic sources:

1. USCCB (United States Conference of Catholic Bishops) Content:
   - Used in accordance with fair use guidelines for educational and religious purposes
   - Commercial use may require additional licensing
   - See: https://www.usccb.org/committees/divine-worship/policies

2. Vatican Official Documents:
   - Used with proper attribution in accordance with Vatican policies
   - See: https://www.vatican.va

3. Traditional Catholic Prayers:
   - Public domain content
   - Traditional prayers are part of the common heritage of the Catholic Church

4. Third-party Content:
   - All third-party content is used with proper attribution
   - Users should verify licensing requirements for commercial applications

DISCLAIMER:
This software is provided for educational and religious purposes. Users are
responsible for ensuring compliance with all applicable copyright and licensing
requirements when using this software, especially for commercial purposes.

The developers of this software make no warranties about the accuracy,
completeness, or reliability of the liturgical information provided. Users
should consult official Church sources for authoritative liturgical guidance.